<h2>About Bali</h2>h2>
<p>The town of Ubud is the cultural and spiritual center of the Indonesian island of Bali. Ubud was once called “Ubad”, meaning “Medicine” in Balinese, referring not only to the medicinal plants and herbs that grow in abundance here, but also to the healing power of this sacred ground. Ubud has long been known for its powerful curative energy, and for centuries, people have flocked to this oasis for healing. </p>
<p>Ubud is also a showcase of culinary inventiveness. And when it comes to raw, vegan food you find the very best that the world has to offer. The ministry of tourism has nominated Ubud as a world “gastronomy destination”, making it the first in the world to receive a designation from the United Nations World Tourism Organization for culinary excellence.</p>
<p>Colorful offerings of flowers and incense adorning each street corner, calming the eyes and mind, and the seductive nature of this town can easily turn a short holiday into a stay of months or even years. </p>
<h3>VISA</h3>
<p>If you are staying less than 30 days you can get free entry stamp upon arrival at the Airport in Bali. If you are staying longer, you will need to get a visa on arrival, which you can also get at the airport, or a social/tourist visa which you need to apply for from the Indonesian embassy of your country before your trip.</p>
<p><br /> VISA OPTIONS</p>
<p>Below is a summary of Visa options to Indonesia (please check to make sure whether this is applicable to your country of citizenship).</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Free Entry</strong> - For a majority of countries, entry into Indonesia is free of charge, valid for 30 days. This is NOT extentable.</li>
<li><strong>Visa on Arrival</strong> &ndash; You can get a 30-day Visa-on Arrival at the airport when you arrive. The price is $35 USD and it is valid for 30 days This visa can be extended ONCE for another 30 days).</li>
<li><strong>Social or Tourist Visa</strong> - This Visa is valid for 60 days and can be extended up to 3 times, for 30 days each. It is issued by consulate or embassy of Indonesia in your home country and needs to be applied for, and issued in your home country before travelling.</li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<p>Please note:</p>
<ul>
<li>The Free Visa and Visa on Arrival is not valid for one month. It&rsquo;s 30 days only. The day of arrival counts as one day, and the day of departure also counts as a full day. If you overstay you will be charged a penalty of IDR 1,000,000 per day (subject to change).</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>If you apply for a Social or Tourist Visa, make sure you start the application process in good time before your departure so that all necessary documents ready on time.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Our Alchemy Academy visa agent can help with the extension of Visa on Arrival and Social or Tourist Visa if you wish to stay longer.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>For exact information about visa, and what applies to your country, please contact the Indonesian Embassy in your home country. Please double check with the indonesian embassy of your country what is applicable to your country of citizenship. Or check the immigration website of Indonesia: www.imigrasi.go.id.</li>
</ul>
